cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, q-bio.GN, q-bio.QM 

The paper discusses the use of computational intelligence tools for DNA sequence analysis in bioinformatics, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of big biological data, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different methods for evaluation, which could be related to q-bio.GN (Genomics) and q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods).
